   A http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/native_client/trunk/src/native_client/tests/toolchain/method_pointer_repr.cc?r1=11454&amp;r2=11453&amp;pathrev=11454
   M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/native_client/trunk/src/native_client/tests/toolchain/nacl.scons?r1=11454&amp;r2=11453&amp;pathrev=11454

PNaCl: Add a test to check the representation of C++ method pointers

This is in preparation for changing pnacl-clang to use the ARM
representation instead of the x86/Itanium representation, since the
former doesn't assume that function pointers are 0 mod 2.  The
x86/Itanium representation assumes it can use the bottom bit of a
function pointer as a tag bit.

The test also checks that C++ method pointers work.

BUG=https://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3450
TEST=run_method_pointer_repr_test

